messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /admin/seed

HTTP methods acceptance (based on the code):
- All methods acceptable: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The AdminController class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so there is no additional prefix to the method-level paths.
- The seed() handler method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/admin/seed", method = RequestMethod.POST). That explicitly maps only POST requests to the path "/admin/seed".
- Because the code explicitly maps POST only, no other HTTP methods (GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE, OPTIONS, HEAD) are declared as accepted in the source. Per the instruction to base acceptance on the code (not on runtime framework behavior), only POST is marked acceptable.
